  "prompt": "What does \"last activity\" mean on Skype?",
  "response": "\"Last activity\" on Skype refers to the last time a user was actively using the Skype app or was logged into the Skype service. It gives an indication of when they were last online and potentially available to communicate.\n\nHere's a breakdown of what it can mean:\n\n*   **They were actively using Skype:** This includes sending messages, making calls, changing their status, browsing contacts, etc.\n*   **Their Skype app was open and connected to the internet:** Even if they weren't actively doing anything, if their Skype app was running in the foreground or background and connected to the internet, it could register as activity.\n*   **They were logged into Skype on another device:** If they were logged into Skype on their phone, computer, or tablet, even if they weren't actively using it on that specific device, it could still show as activity.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **It's not always perfectly accurate:** Skype may not always update the \"last activity\" status in real-time. There can be delays or inconsistencies.\n*   **Users can hide their status:** Skype allows users to set their status to \"Invisible,\" which hides their \"last activity\" time from others.  In this case, it will usually say \"Last seen a long time ago\" or not display a time at all.\n*   **\"Last seen\" vs. \"Online\":** \"Last activity\" is different from being \"Online.\" \"Online\" means the user is currently active on Skype. \"Last activity\" refers to the last time they were active, even if they are now offline.\n\nIn summary, \"last activity\" is a helpful but not always foolproof indicator of when someone was last using Skype. It's a good starting point to gauge their availability, but don't rely on it as absolute truth.\n",
